doc.after: From October 2010 through September 2011, both major reporting stations in Austin, Camp Mabry and Bergstrom Int'l, had the least rainfall of a water year on record, receiving less than a third of normal precipitation.[69] This was a result of La NiÃ±a conditions in the eastern Pacific Ocean where water was significantly cooler than normal.
